Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaurianne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aurianne</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/30/02 5:13:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12245.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: new wizzy spires</span><hr size=1> Well... they are partly right. To move the pyramid they'd have to do two things...<br>
<br>
1. They'd have to edit the S3D file for the zone. This would then have to be downloaded. That's the 7MB of the download.<br>
<br>
2. They'd have to change the SPDAT.EFF to change the location it drops you in.<br>
<br>
<br>
Now. Unfortunately, it's utterly impossible for them to just do a hotpatch which changes the location of the pyramid model live every time you load the zone. The engine just isn't capable of that kind of hot modification.<br>
<br>
However, they don't have to move the pyramid to move the port. It does not require a massive 7MB patch for them to add a new spell, or just change the coordinates that it ports in. Witness the patch where they added the SFG port as well as the velious gates. I seem to recall only downloading a new DirectX 8 graphics engine and SPDAT.EFF with that one.<br>
<br>
The problem is... This is a roleplaying game. And they can't really give a good roleplaying reason for it to move. The blunt line is simple: If the port was so junky, then why would so many arcane scientists have wasted their time creating the spell which teleported you there?<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Personally, I wouldn't move the WK pyramid. I'd have the scientists of Erud or Qeynos decide that they want a ride closer to Qeynos, and find some way to anchor to the ruins in the NE corner of Qeynos hills. Once they'd done that, boom. port-in.<br>
<br>
<br>
Of course, it's a pipe dream. VI has already announced that they aren't going to change it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=12245.topic&index=16><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=12245.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=12245.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=12245.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=12245.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub23.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm1">General Discussion<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm3">Trade Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm4">Rant Forum<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm8">Mob Dropped Spells<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm10">Class Balance & Class Bugs<option value="graffeswizardcompilationfrm38">Discussion of Inter-Species Tensio